WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.145
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:07.145 --> 00:00:08.770
JESSICA HARROP: Hi,
I'm Jessica and I'm

00:00:08.770 --> 00:00:10.853
going to be talking about
a chemical demonstration

00:00:10.853 --> 00:00:14.030
today that I like to call
"Death of a Gummy Bear."

00:00:17.960 --> 00:00:19.760
We eat these little
guys all the time

00:00:19.760 --> 00:00:21.410
and our bodies
break down the sugar

00:00:21.410 --> 00:00:23.837
in a series of
chemical reactions.

00:00:23.837 --> 00:00:26.420
But what happens when you break
down the sugar in a gummy bear

00:00:26.420 --> 00:00:28.340
outside of our bodies?

00:00:28.340 --> 00:00:33.130
Well, MIT'S Dr. John
Dolhun is going to show us.

00:00:33.130 --> 00:00:36.350
Here he is at the Cambridge
Science Festival at MIT.

00:00:36.350 --> 00:00:39.740
JOHN DOLHUN: Now I'm
going to actually

00:00:39.740 --> 00:00:43.470
be combusting a gummy candy.

00:00:43.470 --> 00:00:46.301
And my wife said, please
don't tell them it's a bear.

00:00:46.301 --> 00:00:46.800
Guess what?

00:00:46.800 --> 00:00:48.240
